      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i just sit here thinking about how much energy it takes to actually exist... like, every single thing we do, every struggle, every single feeling, it's all just happening on a tiny speck in a void that doesn't care. in a billion years, none of this will have happened. it feels like such a huge, exhausting waste of effort. does it even make sense to keep trying when the math of the universe just says everything is destined to be nothing anyway?",
